  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promote access to justice for displaced older south Sudanese (Allen &amp; Overy)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 2: Ensure 1,500 older South Sudanese refugees and IDPs (60% women, 5% persons with disabilities) are protected against violations of rights by 2020 through the provision of legal aid services

The second objective will be achieved through the provision of centre and home-based legal aid and referral services facilitated by community-based paralegal volunteers. The project will also involve pro-bono legal counselling and advice, in which we would encourage Allen &amp; Overy staff involvement.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Objective 3: Enhance the capacity of 15 humanitarian agencies and law enforcement institutions operating in Adjumani refugee camp and PoCs in Juba to facilitate access to age and disability friendly legal protection for displaced older men and women by 2020

The third objective will be achieved through trainings and review meetings to be conducted among humanitarian agencies operating in the targeted refugee camp and PoCs to enhance awareness on older men and women&apos;s legal rights, their inclusion and access to justice.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The following are the specific objectives of the project:
Objective 1: Enhance the capacity of 50 community-based paralegal volunteers (60% women, 5% persons with disabilities) to provide legal aid services to vulnerable older men and women in Adjumani refugee camp in Uganda and two PoCs in Juba by 2020

The first objective on capacity building of community-based paralegal volunteers will be achieved through identification and training of volunteers from the refugee community to provide the service. This will be done in consultation with existing community-based structures such as the refugee welfare committee (RWC)6, existing older persons&apos; associations (OPAs)7, persons with disability organizations and the general refugee community. Selected volunteers will be trained using existing paralegal training manuals, which will be revised with the support of this project.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aim is to ensure age friendly access to legal protection of displaced older South Sudanese men and women that are affected by conflict in Uganda and South Sudan. This will be achieved through the provision of both centre-based and home-based legal aid and referral services, and capacity building of humanitarian actors on legal protection of displaced older people. The project is therefore in alignment with the Allen &amp; Overy&apos;s core theme of access to justice.</narrative>
  </description>
